  <source>Hospital de Clinicas de Porto Alegre</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary hypothesis of this trial is that changes in oral vitamin K intake, based on
      simple food registries, may be superior to conventional changes in doses of medications in
      order to stabilize chronic oral anticoagulation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
